{
  "article_id": "DemocraticHerald1901",
  "paragraphs": [
    [
      {
        "text": "THE story of "
      },
      {
        "text": "the Indian woman",
        "entity_key": "lw",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": " left alone on the "
      },
      {
        "text": "island of San Nicolas",
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": " for nearly twenty years has been written by a number of romancers who gave but little heed to fact and free reign to imagination. From occurences that have passed into history and are known to be authentic, this tale is drawn."
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "The ",
        "tropes": [
          3
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "aborigines of San Nicolas Island",
        "tropes": [
          3
        ],
        "entity_key": "natam_NicolenoTongva",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": "were supposed to be of ",
        "tropes": [
          3
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "Aztec",
        "tropes": [
          3
        ],
        "entity_key": "natam_aztec",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": " or ",
        "tropes": [
          3
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "Toltec",
        "tropes": [
          3
        ],
        "entity_key": "natam_toltecs",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": " origin,",
        "tropes": [
          3
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": " a peaceable people like all tribes Indigenous to the tropics."
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "War with the savage ",
        "tropes": [
          11
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "Alaskan Indians",
        "tropes": [
          11
        ],
        "entity_keys": [
          "natam_aleuts",
          "natam_kodiak"
        ],
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": " had nearly exterminated ",
        "tropes": [
          11
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the Indians of San Nicholas",
        "tropes": [
          11
        ],
        "entity_key": "natam_NicolenoTongva",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": " when ",
        "tropes": [
          11
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the Catholic fathers",
        "tropes": [
          11
        ],
        "entity_key": "misfats",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": " who founded ",
        "tropes": [
          11
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the missions",
        "tropes": [
          11
        ],
        "entity_key": "mi_mainlandmissions",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": " on ",
        "tropes": [
          11
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the mainland",
        "tropes": [
          11
        ],
        "entity_key": "re_mld",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": " desired to bring ",
        "tropes": [
          11
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the few remaining natives",
        "tropes": [
          11
        ],
        "entity_key": "natam_NicolenoTongva",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": " across ",
        "tropes": [
          11
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the channel",
        "tropes": [
          11
        ],
        "entity_key": "re_sbchannel",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": " that they might teach them the Christian religion.",
        "tropes": [
          11
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": " Accordingly, after repeated efforts to accomplish this, "
      },
      {
        "text": "a schooner",
        "entity_key": "sh_peoresnada",
        "entity_type": "ship"
      },
      {
        "text": " was sent to "
      },
      {
        "text": "the island",
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": " in 1836 for this purpose. Some time was consumed in gathering together "
      },
      {
        "text": "these people",
        "entity_key": "natam_NicolenoTongva",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": " and their effects."
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "As "
      },
      {
        "text": "the last boat",
        "entity_key": "sh_peoresnada",
        "entity_type": "ship"
      },
      {
        "text": " was leaving the strand, "
      },
      {
        "text": "a woman",
        "entity_key": "lw",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "with "
      },
      {
        "text": "a young babe",
        "entity_key": "lwchild",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "in her arms sprang on shore. "
      },
      {
        "text": "Her little girl",
        "entity_key": "lwchild",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ", a child of eight years, had slipped from her side in the confusion—gone probably in search of some remembered trinket dear to her childish heart—or, perhaps, run away, overcome with terror at the unusual migration of "
      },
      {
        "text": "her people",
        "entity_key": "bhagroup",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "."
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "The woman",
        "entity_key": "lw",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": " besought them to await her return, and hastened over the hill, calling as she went. The moments passed—the white man is ever impatient, and he grumbled at the delay. An hour went by, but "
      },
      {
        "text": "the woman",
        "entity_key": "lw",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "had not returned. The wind was rising rapidly, and a storm was imminent. "
      },
      {
        "text": "The schooner",
        "entity_key": "sh_peoresnada",
        "entity_type": "ship"
      },
      {
        "text": " had signaled them twice in the last half hour. The waters about "
      },
      {
        "text": "the island",
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": " were shoal, and there was no safe anchorage along its shores. The waves were running high upon the ledges surrounding the little bay, and their crests were white with the foam of action. "
      },
      {
        "text": "The ship",
        "entity_key": "sh_peoresnada",
        "entity_type": "ship"
      },
      {
        "text": " signalled again, and with a muttered imprecation and a gruff command, the boat pushed off to join "
      },
      {
        "text": "the tossing vessel",
        "entity_key": "sh_peoresnada",
        "entity_type": "ship"
      },
      {
        "text": "."
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "As soon as all were on board, "
      },
      {
        "text": "Captain Hubbard",
        "entity_key": "chu",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": " weighed anchor and stood away for deep water. When "
      },
      {
        "text": "the relatives and friends",
        "entity_key": "bhagroup",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": " learned that "
      },
      {
        "text": "the woman",
        "entity_key": "lw",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": " had been left behind, they besought "
      },
      {
        "text": "the captain",
        "entity_key": "chu",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": " with many tears, and with pleadings in their own tongue, to return and bring her away."
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "The gale increased in fury and continued unabated for the space of a week. "
      },
      {
        "text": "The heavy-laden schooner",
        "entity_key": "sh_peoresnada",
        "entity_type": "ship"
      },
      {
        "text": " labored hard, and disaster threatened."
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "When "
      },
      {
        "text": "San Pedro",
        "entity_key": "ci_sp",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": " Harbor was finally reached, the "
      },
      {
        "text": "San Nicholas Indians",
        "entity_key": "bhagroup",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "were distributed between "
      },
      {
        "text": "Los Angeles",
        "entity_key": "mi_losangeles",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": " and "
      },
      {
        "text": "San Gabriel",
        "entity_key": "mi_sgabriel",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": " missions, and "
      },
      {
        "text": "Captain Hubbard",
        "entity_key": "chu",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": " departed for "
      },
      {
        "text": "Monterey",
        "entity_key": "ci_mo",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", where he had orders to take on a cargo of lumber for "
      },
      {
        "text": "San Francisco",
        "entity_key": "ci_sf",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "."
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "On reaching "
      },
      {
        "text": "the Golden Gate",
        "entity_key": "re_thegoldengate",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", in rough weather, "
      },
      {
        "text": "the improperly laden craft",
        "entity_key": "sh_peoresnada",
        "entity_type": "ship"
      },
      {
        "text": " capsized and was eventually blown out to sea, and is supposed to have been taken by "
      },
      {
        "text": "a Russian vessel",
        "entity_key": "sh_russian",
        "entity_type": "ship"
      },
      {
        "text": ". The crew reached shore in safety, and it was always Captain Hubbard's intention to return to "
      },
      {
        "text": "San Nicolas",
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": " for "
      },
      {
        "text": "the lost woman",
        "entity_key": "lw",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ". "
      },
      {
        "text": "There was now no craft of any description except open boats and Indian canoes from ",
        "tropes": [
          12
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "San Francisco",
        "tropes": [
          12
        ],
        "entity_key": "ci_sf",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": " to ",
        "tropes": [
          12
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "San Diego",
        "tropes": [
          12
        ],
        "entity_key": "ci_sd",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", and no one could be found willing to risk a voyage to ",
        "tropes": [
          12
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "San Nicolas",
        "tropes": [
          12
        ],
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": " in one of these.",
        "tropes": [
          12
        ]
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "It was generally known along the coast of "
      },
      {
        "text": "California",
        "entity_key": "st_cal",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": " that "
      },
      {
        "text": "an Indian woman",
        "entity_key": "lw",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": " and "
      },
      {
        "text": "her children",
        "entity_key": "lwchild",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": " had been left upon the Island of "
      },
      {
        "text": "San Nicholas",
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", but as time passed and they were not rescued, it came to be generally believed that all had perished. Fifteen years slipped by, and in the spring of 1851 "
      },
      {
        "text": "Captain Nidever",
        "entity_key": "gni",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ", of "
      },
      {
        "text": "Santa Barbara",
        "entity_key": "ci_sb",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", with "
      },
      {
        "text": "one other white man",
        "entity_key": "tje",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": " and a small crew of "
      },
      {
        "text": "Mission Indians",
        "entity_key": "natam_missionindians",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": ", visited "
      },
      {
        "text": "San Nicolas",
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": " in "
      },
      {
        "text": "a schooner",
        "entity_key": "sh_nidever",
        "entity_type": "ship"
      },
      {
        "text": " in search of otter. They made a landing at the eastern end of "
      },
      {
        "text": "the island",
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", and walked along the southern shore a distance of five miles or more. "
      },
      {
        "text": "Captain Nidever",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ],
        "entity_key": "gni",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "discovered footprints of a human being soon after landing. These were no doubt made when the ground had been soaked by the previous winter rains, for the impressions were deep and quite dry and hard. The footprints were small, and ",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the captain",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ],
        "entity_key": "gni",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "felt convinced that they were made by a woman. A short distance from the shore were found several circular, roofless huts made of brush, about six feet in height and the same in diameter. These enclosures were fully a mile apart, and near them were stakes of driftwood driven in the ground, from which were suspended pieces of seal's blubber out of the reach of wild animals. The blubber was comparatively fresh, and had no doubt been placed there but a few weeks previous.",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ]
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "Captain Nidever",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ],
        "entity_key": "gni",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": " had landed upon ",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "San Nicolas",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ],
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": " early in the morning, intending to remain during the day to search for seal and otter, but near noon a northwester began blowing, and he hastened back to ",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the schooner",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ],
        "entity_key": "sh_nidever",
        "entity_type": "ship"
      },
      {
        "text": ". Here they remained at anchor for eight days in the lee of ",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the island",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ],
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", the sea being at times so rough and the wind so fierce that he expected momentarily to be driven from his anchorage. When the storm abated sufficiently, ",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "Captain Nidever",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ],
        "entity_key": "gni",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": " returned to ",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "Santa Barbara",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ],
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": " without again landing [upon ",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the island",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ],
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ".",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ]
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "The next year he once more visited] ",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "San Nicholas",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ],
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": " for game, landing near the same place as on his previous voyage. He and ",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the ship's mate",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ],
        "entity_key": "cdi",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": " explored ",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the island",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ],
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": " nearly to its western extremity. The blubber found on the previous visit had been replaced by a fresh stock. In the crotch of a tree near the west end of ",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the island",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ],
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": " they found a basket containing a garment made of the skins of the cormorant, cut in squares and neatly pieced together; with the ends of the feathers all pointing downward.",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": " There were shell hooks, bone needles, a rope of sinew, and various trinkets in the basket with the robe. These things "
      },
      {
        "text": "Captain Nidever",
        "entity_key": "gni",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": " scattered upon the ground, thinking if they were replaced on his next visit to the the tree it would be conclusive evidence that "
      },
      {
        "text": "the woman",
        "entity_key": "cdi",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": " was still alive. "
      },
      {
        "text": "After several days spent in securing seal and otter upon the ground already explored, another wind storm came on, and the spot containing the basket was not revisited; as on all previous voyages, ",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the woman",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ],
        "entity_key": "lw",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": " was left to her fate and ",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the schooner",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ],
        "entity_key": "sh_nidever",
        "entity_type": "ship"
      },
      {
        "text": " crossed to ",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "San Miguel Island",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ],
        "entity_key": "i_sm",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": " without her.",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ]
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "In July, 1853, ",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "Captain Nidever",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ],
        "entity_key": "gni",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": " again went to ",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "San Nicolas",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ],
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", determined to rescue ",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the woman",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ],
        "entity_key": "lw",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": " if she could be found. Before, he had gone to find otter and seal; now he had a nobler quest.",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ]
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "He anchored midway of the northwestern shore of ",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the island",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ],
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", near ",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "Corral Harbor",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ],
        "entity_key": "re_coralharbor",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", where ",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the natives",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ],
        "entity_key": "bhagroup",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": " had embarked in 1836. At this point and at the western extremity of ",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the island",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ],
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": " is found an abundance of good water, seal and fish. Here ",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "Captain Nidever",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ],
        "entity_key": "gni",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": " made camp, and with ",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "his men",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ],
        "entity_keys": [
          "cdi",
          "col",
          "cook",
          "msh",
          "poli",
          "nsk",
          "hva"
        ],
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": " began a systematic search. On the second day a hut was discovered upon the ridge, and on approaching it, piles of ashes and bones were seen at its entrance.",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ]
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "Within the enclosure sat ",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the object of their search",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ],
        "entity_key": "lw",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ", talking aloud to herself, and with a rude knife, manufactured from a piece of rusty iron hoop, washed up by the waves, she was diligently scraping blubber from a piece of sealskin.",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ]
